name: Chicken Zucchini Enchiladas
author: bd.weld
summary: A low-carb approach to enchiladas with zucchini tortillas.
ingredients: 1 ⅓ cups green enchilada sauce, divided
1 (4 ounce) can chopped Hatch chile peppers, drained
1 cup shredded Cheddar-Monterey Jack cheese blend
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C)
Heat oil in a large skillet over medium heat
Add onion and cook until soft, about 5 minutes
Add garlic, cumin, chili powder, and oregano
Add shredded chicken, 1 cup enchilada sauce, and green chiles
Slice zucchini into thin, wide sheets using a vegetable peeler or a mandoline
Lay out 3 zucchini slices, slightly overlapping, and place a spoonful of the chicken mixture on top
Roll up and transfer to a baking dish
Repeat with remaining zucchini and chicken mixture
Spread remaining 1/3 cup enchilada sauce over zucchini enchiladas
Bake in the preheated oven until cheese has melted, about 20 minutes
